An Oredo Magistrates’ Court in Benin City on Monday, sentenced a 34-year-old, Wisdom Sakpra to one year in prison for stealing the sum of N110,000 The Magistrate, Ivie Akere sentenced Sakpra after the convict had pleaded guilty to a two-count charge of conspiracy and stealing filed against him. Akere sentenced the convict to six months on each count charge and did not give him an option of fine to served as a deterrent to others. Earlier, the police prosecutor, ASP Patrick Agbonifo told the court that the convict on Jan 23, , 2020 at First Bank in Adesuwa Junction, Sapele road in Benin , was arrested at the scene of the crime. According to the prosecutor, the convict and others at large specialized in robbing customers that go to bank for withdrawals. He said that the convict did unlawfully stole the total of N110,000, a property of Andrew Igbodidi and the convict also confessed that he had robbed another victim, Ehis Unemhin close to UBA at Textile Mill road, Benin, adding that he used a handkerchief to clean victim’s face. He said after the convict had used the handkerchief to clean victims face, the victim obeyed all instruction and directives given by the convict. He added that his victim, Unemhin was invited by the police and he confirmed the convict statement. The prosecutor said the offence contravened the provision of sections 516, and 390(9) of the Criminal Code Cap. 48 Vol. 11, Laws of the defunct Bendel State of Nigeria, 1976, now applicable in Edo.